dismissalText.commentary: Babar Azam c Hales b Rashid 51 (51b 5x4 1x6 65m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Hales holds on this time! Azam aiming to clear deep cover, gets too far underneath the ball and can't get the distance on his shot. Hales comes in from deep cover - he has to be aware of two other fielders close by - and holds a good catch as he slides on his knees. He's pumped with that.
tossed up, driven, into the bread-basket, it's nearly over now ...
battered into the deep, and that is easy pickings for Woakes at wide long-on. Nearly done

headshotImage.longCaption: Anwar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: tossed up, driven, plucked low at short cover, and England have sealed the series! Or have they? A quick check upstairs to make sure it carried, but the fielders are in little doubt. A pretty futile faff, the umpire's soft signal was out, and sure enough, it is!

commentTextItems.html: tossed up, driven, plucked low at short cover, and England have sealed the series! Or have they? A quick check upstairs to make sure it carried, but the fielders are in little doubt. A pretty futile faff, the umpire's soft signal was out, and sure enough, it is!

commentPostTextItems.html: 10.12pm Handshakes all round, and quite an achievement from England to seal this series, especially after a pretty heavy thumping in the opening contest. The hero of the hour, none other than Jos Buttler, whose turbo-charged century put England out of reach. It was a valiant chase in the circumstances, but 46-ball centuries are generally hard to trump ...

atifsardarkhan: "Only website where you come across the most interesting comments. I'm sure many others would come for the same reason :D BTW! WELL PLAYED TEAM ENGLAND and hope our team find some better middle order players." You're very welcome, it's been a pleasure ...

So, England win by 84 runs, and claim an impressive 3-1 series win. If Buttler isn't the Man of the Match I will eat the TV. Have a read of George Dobell's match report, being uploaded as we speak. From Gnasher and myself, goodnight and don't forget to tune back in next week for the tour finale, the T20 series.

commentTextItems.html: tossed onto a good length, fielded inadvertently by the non-striker, Irfan

commentPostTextItems.html: A maiden over. A rare moment of calm in a bat-frenzied contest

headshotImage.caption: Anwar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Anwar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: bouncer! Grrr ... did well to get it that high, to be fair. Irfan turns his head and wears it on the armpit
forward and defended into the covers
on the back foot, and angled into the covers

commentPreTextItems.html: Ali: "Can anwar snatch the match from England? Its a lot to ask but he did the same with Srilanka" That was also a one-wicket win. <strike>Never say never</strike> ... who am I kidding?

commentTextItems.html: down the track, tapped to midwicket

headshotImage.caption: Anwar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Anwar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Yasir Shah c Woakes b Ali 5 (8b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 62.5

commentTextItems.html: battered into the deep, and that is easy pickings for Woakes at wide long-on. Nearly done

commentPostTextItems.html: David R.: "Pardon the injection of mathematics but it's not less than a run a ball, and Pakistan can't technically win it in singles. The required run-rate is still over 7, and it only briefly dipped below 7 (to 6.85, as I recall)." Fair point, who's actually paying attention at this stage anyway?

commentTextItems.html: half an appeal as Yasir misses a slog sweep
clattered down the ground, lots of intent but the field is set back

commentPostTextItems.html: James Bartholom: "The chase was never going to be easy. England maintained pressure and forced Pakistan to go after the ball, ultimately costing wickets" Troo dat

commentTextItems.html: a play and a miss to complete the over

headshotImage.caption: Anwar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Anwar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: having said that, there is a horrid static hoick from deep in the crease, and David Willey running in from deep long-on can't quite get his fingers under the ball. Or maybe he does, as he is in a significant amount of pain. That could smart ...

commentPostTextItems.html: A break in play as Willey gets patched up. Pakistan could get em in singles, theoretically ...

commentTextItems.html: on the pads, a gentle clip out to the leg-side. There is a serenity so far about this partnership, as if they have twigged that it is less than a run a ball ...
driven on the up to midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: Muneeb: "I know its pretty much over but my heart is still saying we can win.. Bleed green" You ought to get that checked out. Could be gangrene ...
